text: Paramore Hill is an unincorporated community in Jenkins County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== Paramore was the name of an early settler. A variant name was "Paramore". A post office called Parramore Hill was established in 1868, the name was changed to Parramore in 1881, and the post office closed in 1900. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Jenkins County, Georgia
title: Paramore Hill, Georgia
